text.tspan: Rate of new cervical cancer cases, 2022
Estimated number of new cervical cancer cases per 100,000 women.

Note: To allow for comparisons between countries and over time, this metric is
age-standardized
. The methods of estimation are
country-specific, and the quality of the national estimates depends on the coverage, accuracy, and timeliness of the recorded incidence and
mortality data in a given country.
